{
  "doc_id": "51923",
  "text": "Postoperative recurrence is observed in a high proportion of CD patients after resection, reaching 79% after 6 years of follow-up [CITATION_1] . Risk factors for postoperative recurrence in Crohn's disease are considered to be: active smoking, penetrating behavior, perianal lesions, prior intestinal resection, extensive small bowel disease [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] .",
